    "headline": "TSMC boss bets big on AI growth, says he'd 'like' to hike chip prices",
    "summary": "<body><p>STORY: The world's largest contract chipmaker TSMC says it's confident in its growth over the next few years...</p><p>thanks to robust demand for computing power and advanced semiconductors as it rides a relentless AI boom.</p><p>The Taiwanese firm's CEO spoke at its annual shareholders meeting on Thursday.</p><p>C.C. Wei said customers are still positive on the outlook for AI, although the company continues to monitor the impact of rising component costs.</p><p>Asked whether TSMC could raise prices for customers, Wei said the firm would like to do that as, quote, \"we still need to make money.\"</p><p>Taiwan plays a crucial role in the global AI supply chain for companies including Nvidia &nbsp;and Apple.</p><p>And its position is anchored by TSMC.</p><p>The tech giant said it was working hard to meet all customer demands...</p><p>although added that it will take a \"very long time\" to fully satisfy American customers' needs with production in the U.S.</p><p>Looking ahead, Wei said he views autonomous vehicles as long-term growth drivers.</p><p>But TSMC faces political risk as China steps up military pressure on democratically and separately governed Taiwan...</p><p>which Beijing views as Chinese territory.</p></body>",
